interactions.flavorLineOne: You have become a Legend in the Crucible. Shaxx wishes to bask in your glory.
Your efforts in the Crucible have become Legend. Time to begin your story anew.
Shaxx is impressed by your commitment to your Bond. Your zeal, your fury, your undeniable charisma… The two of you are an awe-inspiring team. Keep spreading the love.
As boisterous as ever, Shaxx speaks warmly (and loudly) of Crimson Days—and of his challenge to Guardians who choose to celebrate with him in the Crucible.
Lord Shaxx has a gift for you: a Ghost Shell that will track your victories.
It seems unlikely that Shaxx will remove his helmet to consume the cookies, but that doesn't mean he isn't grateful.
Shaxx, looking even more animated than usual, welcomes you to a new world of Valor and Glory—and encourages you to test your prowess in the newly ranked Crucible.

Lord Shaxx is impressed when you return. "The Crucible is fast-paced, even chaotic at times," he says. "That you can pull off such a careful, precise shot under those conditions… Anyone on the other side of your scope should be worried. Well done!"

Now that you've had a taste of the Crucible, Shaxx is eager to see what you've really got. 

Each week, answer Shaxx's Call to Arms by completing matches in the Crucible to earn valuable rewards.
Lord Shaxx's voice already sounds better even though the package of lozenges remains unopened. Still, he seems grateful.
Shaxx congratulates you and your Crimson Bond on battles hard-fought and victories hard-won during Crimson Days—and offers a handsome reward with his inspiring words.
As you are a Fabled competitor in the Crucible, Shaxx wishes to reward your efforts.

Victory is about more than just winning a match. Shaxx knows the power of a symbol.

He challenges you to win a Crucible match wearing full Season 4 Crucible armor.
Shaxx sees in you a kindred spirit. He congratulates you on your mighty and dazzling victory.
"I had a feeling I'd be handing this over to you," Shaxx booms. He collects your new Recluse and hands it over with a respectful nod. "Do the children proud."
"We have all borne witness to your journey, Guardian. But I know you still have some things undone. Use this to finish what they started." —Lord Shaxx, to Josef
"She used to glow with pride when you'd return from a match." —Lord Shaxx, to Josef
"Your old life is over, Redrix. This is different from your birth as an Exo and your rebirth as a Guardian. Now, you are an icon. Let that guide your future." —Lord Shaxx
Shaxx looks at you differently now. He offers you the weapon he used those many years ago at Twilight Gap, and wishes you well when you carry it into battle.

Lord Shaxx oversees the Crucible, a tournament that trains Guardians by pitting them against one another in friendly competition. Though the future of the Crucible was in doubt after the fall of the City, Shaxx is convinced that it is needed now more than ever. 

Complete matches in the Crucible to hone your skills against other players and earn rewards.
Complete Crucible matches and challenges to get Crucible tokens and earn Level 20 rewards from this faction.
Your reputation in the Crucible precedes you. Take this reward in recognition of your deeds.

Show Lord Shaxx proof of your deeds in the Crucible.
